下来。她肯定一直在晒日光浴到很晚，因为她进来时基本上都是穿着比基尼和被子。”</p><p> <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/adele-extends-las-vegas-residency-with-32-more-shows-3518855">阿黛尔 (Adele) 延长拉斯维加斯驻场演出时间并增加了 32 场演出，该消息</a>首先出现在<a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a>上。</p> ;
罢工演员被警告不要在万圣节盛装打扮https://www.nme.com/news/film/striking-actors-warned-not-to-dress-up-for-halloween-3518862?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=striking-actors-warned-not-to-万圣节装扮Max PilleyFri, 20 Oct 2023 19:09:53 +0000 Film NewsNewsTV News https://www.nme.com/?p=3518862 <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/sagaftra_strike.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="SAG-AFTRA 罢工" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/sagaftra_strike.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/sagaftra_strike-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/sagaftra_strike-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/sagaftra_strike-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/sagaftra_strike-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/sagaftra_strike-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p>表演工会已告知其成员，任何此类服装都会宣传与演员有争议的工作室制作的内容。</p><p> <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/film/striking-actors-warned-not-to-dress-up-for-halloween-3518862">警告演员不要在万圣节盛装打扮的帖子</a>首先出现在<a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">《NME》</a>上。</p> ; <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/sagaftra_strike.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="SAG-AFTRA 罢工" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/sagaftra_strike.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/sagaftra_strike-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/sagaftra_strike-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/sagaftra_strike-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/sagaftra_strike-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/sagaftra_strike-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p>引人注目的演员被警告不要在今年万圣节打扮成电影或电视节目中的角色。 </p><ul><li data-leveltext="" data-font="Symbol" data-listid="10" data-list-defn-props="{&quot;335552541&quot;:1,&quot;335559683&quot;:0,&quot;335559684&quot;:-2,&quot;335559685&quot;:720,&quot;335559991&quot;:360,&quot;469769226&quot;:&quot;Symbol&quot;,&quot;469769242&quot;:[8226],&quot;469777803&quot;:&quot;left&quot;,&quot;469777804&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;469777815&quot;:&quot;hybridMultilevel&quot;}" aria-setsize="-1" data-aria-posinset="1" data-aria-level="1"><b>阅读更多：</b><b> </b><a href="https://www.nme.com/features/film-features/strike-actors-writers-hollywood-when-will-it-end-3477098"><b>好莱坞罢工！关于演员和作家抗议的每个问题都得到了解答</b></a></li></ul><p>SAG-AFTRA 工会已告知其成员，任何此类服装都会宣传与演员有争议的工作室制作的内容。</p><p> “选择受一般角色和人物（幽灵、僵尸、蜘蛛等）启发的服装，”SAG-AFTRA 向其 160,000 名会员发表的一份声明中写道。它还补充说，他们不应该“在社交媒体上发布受打击内容启发的服装照片。”</p><p> “让我们利用集体力量向罢工的雇主发出响亮而明确的信息，即在没有公平合同的情况下，我们不会推广他们的内容！”</p><p>预计以<a href="https://www.nme.com/films/barbie"><em>《芭比娃娃》</em></a>和<a href="https://www.nme.com/series/wednesday"><em>《星期三》</em></a>中的角色为基础的服装将成为今年最受欢迎的万圣节服装之一。去年的<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/check-out-the-best-celebrity-costumes-of-halloween-2022-3339394">亮点包括莉佐扮演玛吉·辛普森和迪迪扮演<em>《黑暗骑士》中希斯·莱杰的小丑。</em></a></p><p> <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/film/why-are-actors-striking-in-hollywood-3468340">SAG-AFTRA（演员工会-美国电视和广播艺术家联合会）于 7 月 14 日开始罢工，</a>原因是与电影和电视制片人联盟 (AMPTP) 之间持续存在劳资纠纷。双方于 10 月 2 日重新启动谈判，但在 10 月 11 日再次破裂，工作室表示谈判“不再让我们朝着积极的方向发展”。</p><p>到目前为止，双方尚未就协议达成一致，SAG-AFTRA 要求增加薪酬、分享流媒体收入以及防止演员的图像和声音被人工智能复制。自罢工开始以来，主要制片厂的大部分美国电影和电视制作都已暂停。</p><p>代表编剧的美国工会美国作家协会近几个月也参与了罢工行动， <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/film/wga-amptp-reach-tentative-deal-end-hollywood-writers-strike-3503437">但这场纠纷于 9 月 27 日结束。</a></p><p> According to the <em>Hollywood Reporter,</em> a Zoom meeting was held on October 17 between union leaders and a group of leading Hollywood stars, including <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/george-clooney">George Clooney</a> , <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/scarlett-johansson">Scarlett Johansson</a> and <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/robert-de-niro">Robert De Niro</a> . The actors suggested that higher earners could pay more in union fees, which they estimated would generate $50 million (£41 million) a year.</p><p> In response to the suggestion, SAG-AFTRA said, “This generous concept is worthy of consideration, but it is in no way related to and would have no bearing on this present contract or even as a subject of collective bargaining.”</p><p> The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/film/striking-actors-warned-not-to-dress-up-for-halloween-3518862">Striking actors warned not to dress up for Halloween</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
 Morrissey says Capitol are willing to give 'Bonfire Of Teenagers' back to him “for a certain price” https://www.nme.com/news/music/morrissey-says-capitol-are-willing-to-give-bonfire-of-teenagers-back-to-him-for-a-certain-price-3518803?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=morrissey-says-capitol-are-willing-to-give-bonfire-of-teenagers-back-to-him-for-a-certain-priceAnagricel Duran Fri, 20 Oct 2023 18:05:31 +0000 Music NewsNewsIndie https://www.nme.com/?p=3518803 <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Morrissey-performing.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="Morrissey performs live on stage at Wembley Arena on March 14, 2020 in London, England. （吉姆·戴森/盖蒂图片社拍摄）" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Morrissey-performing.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Morrissey-performing-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Morrissey-performing-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Morrissey-performing-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Morrissey-performing-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Morrissey-performing-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> &quot;For me, it was a very personal thing and the fact that it hasn&#39;t been released has been torture&quot;</p><p> The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/morrissey-says-capitol-are-willing-to-give-bonfire-of-teenagers-back-to-him-for-a-certain-price-3518803">Morrissey says Capitol are willing to give &#39;Bonfire Of Teenagers&#39; back to him “for a certain price”</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ; <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Morrissey-performing.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="Morrissey performs live on stage at Wembley Arena on March 14, 2020 in London, England. （吉姆·戴森/盖蒂图片社拍摄）" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Morrissey-performing.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Morrissey-performing-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Morrissey-performing-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Morrissey-performing-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Morrissey-performing-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Morrissey-performing-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> <a href="/artists/morrissey">Morrissey</a> has said that Capitol are willing to give &#39;Bonfire Of Teenagers&#39; back to him “for a certain price”.</p><ul class="post-content-read-more"><li> <strong>READ MORE: <a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/live/morrissey-at-riot-fest-review-chicago-3048341">Morrissey at Riot Fest review – pop&#39;s problematic uncle wisely shuts up and plays the hits</a></strong></li></ul><p> During an interview with <em>Good Day New York</em> today (October 20), the former Smiths frontman opened up about the current situation regarding his album &#39;Bonfire Of Teenagers&#39;. He also performed &#39;Sure Enough The Telephone Rings&#39;, which is the 10th song from the LP.</p><p> Speaking to journalist Rosanna Scotto, Morrissey said: “This album was recorded in January 2021 and Capitol signed it and didn&#39;t release it, but they&#39;re now prepared to give it back to me for a certain price. It&#39;s been quite traumatic and quite sad because when you record something, you want it to be available immediately and it was very much of the time. For me, it was a very personal thing and the fact that it hasn&#39;t been released has been torture.” </p><p><iframe loading="lazy" title="Morrissey on Fox5NY - Part 2 - Interview" width="696" height="392" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/lsSaPVmIOzE?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" allowfullscreen></iframe></p><p><iframe loading="lazy" title="Morrissey on Fox5NY - Part 1 - Sure Enough The Telephone Rings" width="696" height="392" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/X_75xSJfjsA?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" allowfullscreen></iframe></p><p> When asked if there is an idea of when fans may be able to hear it, he said: “I&#39;ve got no idea. It really depends on when they&#39;ll give it back to me and how long it takes and all that nonsense.”</p><p> The singer debuted the track &#39;Bonfire Of Teenagers&#39; – which he said was about “England&#39;s 9/11”, the 2017 Manchester Arena bombing – back in July 2022.</p><p> In October 2022, Morrissey <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/morrisseys-new-album-bonfire-of-teenagers-to-feature-miley-cyrus-iggy-pop-flea-and-more-3338982">announced</a> that &#39;Bonfire of Teenagers&#39; would be released in 2023 through Capitol. In late December, however, the former <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/the-smiths">Smiths</a> frontman said he had <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/morrissey-departs-label-miley-cyrus-taken-off-bonfire-of-teenagers-3371299">“voluntarily withdrawn from any association with Capitol Records”</a> . He also revealed that <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/miley-cyrus">Miley Cyrus</a> , who recorded backing vocals for &#39;Bonfire&#39; track &#39;I Am Veronica&#39; in 2020, had asked to have her vocals removed from the song.</p><p> Morrissey then <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/morrissey-is-quickly-coming-around-to-that-belief-that-capitol-is-sabotaging-his-new-album-3394087">released a statement on his website</a> in which it was asserted that, despite Capitol still maintaining ownership of &#39;Bonfire of Teenagers&#39;, the label would not release it. It comes after <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/morrissey-responds-to-being-dropped-by-his-label-this-news-is-perfectly-in-keeping-with-the-relentless-galvanic-horror-of-2020-2818087">he was dropped by BMG in 2020</a> , months after he released his most recent album, <a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/album/morrissey-i-am-not-a-dog-on-a-chain-review-2623817">&#39;I Am Not A Dog On A Chain&#39;</a> .</p><p> In a statement, the singer said he&#39;s <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/morrissey-is-quickly-coming-around-to-that-belief-that-capitol-is-sabotaging-his-new-album-3394087">starting to think that his former label are intentionally “sabotaging” his new album</a> . A statement wrote: “Morrissey has said that although he does not believe that Capitol Records in Los Angeles signed &#39;Bonfire of Teenagers&#39; in order to sabotage it, he is quickly coming around to that belief.”</p><p> Morrissey also revealed earlier this year that <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/morrissey-has-recorded-a-new-album-called-without-music-the-world-dies-3401844">he recorded a new album called &#39;Without Music The World Dies&#39;</a> and shared its tracklist.</p><p> No release date has been confirmed for the new LP, but <a href="https://www.morrisseycentral.com/messagesfrommorrissey/new-recording">a post on Morrissey&#39;s website</a> detailed that it was recorded at La Fabrique Studios in St-Remy, France and was produced by longtime collaborator Joe Chiccarelli. </p><figure id="attachment_3518839" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3518839" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="size-full wp-image-3518839" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Morrissey-performing-2.jpg" alt="Singer Morrissey performs onstage at Palacio de Los Deportes on March 31, 2017 in Mexico City, Mexico. (Photo by Victor Chavez/WireImage)" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Morrissey-performing-2.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Morrissey-performing-2-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Morrissey-performing-2-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Morrissey-performing-2-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Morrissey-performing-2-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Morrissey-performing-2-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3518839" class="wp-caption-text"> Singer Morrissey performs onstage at Palacio de Los Deportes on March 31, 2017 in Mexico City, Mexico. (Photo by Victor Chavez/WireImage)</figcaption></figure><p> At the end of the album announcement, a notice referenced Morrissey&#39;s recent label troubles, reading: “Capitol Records Los Angeles recently terminated their contract with Morrissey, therefore if any record label or private investor has interest in releasing this project, please contact Donnie Knutson.”</p><p> Earlier this week, Morrissey claimed that the CEO of Capitol Records is trying to derail his career.</p><p> He posted an image of Capitol Records&#39; logo <a href="https://www.morrisseycentral.com/messagesfrommorrissey/capitol-wreckers" target="_blank" rel="noopener">on his website</a> on Sunday (October 15) under the headline “CAPITOL WRECKERS”, but with no basis for his attack.</p><p> He also included a photo of Capitol Music Group Chair and CEO Michelle Jubelirer and wrote: “Hi! I run Capitol Records and if I want to wreck Morrissey&#39;s career no one can stop me. Bye, now!”</p><p> <em>NME</em> has reached out to Capitol Records for comment, with the label yet to provide a response.</p><p> Meanwhile, Morrissey announced recently <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/morrissey-announces-2023-tour-dates-in-asia-and-australia-3479470">new 2023 tour dates in Asia and Australia</a> – see the full list of dates <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/morrissey-announces-2023-tour-dates-in-asia-and-australia-3479470">here</a> . The singer wrapped a <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/morrissey-summer-2023-uk-ireland-tour-tickets-3425160">UK and Ireland headline tour</a> this summer.</p><p> The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/morrissey-says-capitol-are-willing-to-give-bonfire-of-teenagers-back-to-him-for-a-certain-price-3518803">Morrissey says Capitol are willing to give &#39;Bonfire Of Teenagers&#39; back to him “for a certain price”</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
